      <!-- Section 5 -->
      <section id="tool-categories" class="anchor-top">
        <h2>Tool Categories to Include in Your Comparison</h2>
        <p><strong>A thorough GEO tools comparison evaluates candidates from all relevant categories rather than treating the market as a single homogeneous set.</strong> The GEO tool landscape currently spans four broadly distinct categories, and the strongest comparison process includes at least one candidate from each before narrowing to a shortlist.</p>
        <p>The <a href="/best-ai-tools-geo/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">dedicated GEO tool</a> category includes purpose-built platforms designed from the ground up for AI citation measurement. These typically score highest on citation tracking accuracy and platform coverage because those are their core product propositions. They vary considerably on reporting depth and integration maturity depending on their age and funding stage.</p>
        <p>The <a href="/best-aeo-platforms-2026/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">answer engine optimisation platform</a> category overlaps significantly with the GEO tool category but tends to emphasise content structure and entity optimisation recommendations alongside measurement. These tools often include schema audit features as a native capability, making them stronger on the structured-data dimension.</p>
        <p>Established SEO platforms with AI visibility add-ons — including <a href="/semrush-geo/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">SEMrush's GEO features</a> and <a href="/ahrefs-geo/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">Ahrefs' AI answer tracking</a> — benefit from integration with existing SEO workflows and typically score highest on the integrations dimension for teams already invested in those platforms. Their GEO-specific capabilities are generally less deep than dedicated tools, but the total cost of the combined stack may be lower than adding a separate GEO tool.</p>
        <p>The <a href="/best-llm-visibility-tools/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">LLM visibility tool</a> category includes platforms focused specifically on how brands are described and portrayed by large language model responses — emphasising entity accuracy, brand sentiment, and knowledge graph presence rather than citation frequency. These are particularly useful for regulated industries and high-profile brands where how AI describes you matters as much as how often it mentions you.</p>
        <p>For a complete overview of the functional categories within the GEO tool landscape, see the <a href="/geo-tools/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">GEO Tools hub</a>. For the broader context of why tool selection sits within a larger strategic framework, the <a href="/generative-engine-optimisation/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">generative engine optimisation guide</a> is the right starting point.</p>
      </section>

